[{"location":"api/#JCGECore-API","page":"API","title":"JCGECore API","text":"@autodocs Modules = [JCGECore] Order = [:module, :type, :function, :macro, :constant]`","category":"section"},{"location":"usage/#Usage","page":"Usage","title":"Usage","text":"JCGECore defines the canonical model interface: RunSpec, sections, sets, mappings, scenarios, and validation. It contains no solver-specific code.","category":"section"},{"location":"usage/#Typical-workflow","page":"Usage","title":"Typical workflow","text":"using JCGECore\n\nsets = Sets(goods, activities, factors, institutions)\nmappings = Mappings(Dict(a => a for a in activities))\n\nsections = [\n    section(:production, blocks_prod),\n    section(:households, blocks_hh),\n    section(:markets, blocks_mkt),\n]\n\nspec = build_spec(\"MyModel\", sets, mappings, sections)","category":"section"},{"location":"usage/#Validation","page":"Usage","title":"Validation","text":"report = validate_spec(spec)\nreport.ok || error(\"Invalid RunSpec\")","category":"section"},{"location":"usage/#Scenarios","page":"Usage","title":"Scenarios","text":"Use ScenarioSpec to describe deltas relative to a baseline.","category":"section"},{"location":"#JCGECore","page":"Home","title":"JCGECore","text":"<picture>\n  <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"assets/jcge_core_logo_dark.png\">\n  <img src=\"assets/jcge_core_logo_light.png\" alt=\"JCGECore logo\" height=\"150\">\n</picture>\n\nJCGECore is part of the JCGE ecosystem. This page provides the package overview and entry points; the API reference is on the next page.","category":"section"}]
